Louisiana's 64 parishes, FIPS codes, and region designations according to different state agencies and organizations, parish geometry, and parish centers.

Source: R/data.R
louisiana_long.Rd

Louisiana's 64 parishes, FIPS codes, and region designations according to different state agencies and organizations, parish geometry, and parish centers.

Usage

louisiana_long

Format

A data frame/sf object with 393 rows and 16 columns:

GEOID, FIPS

Parish FIPS code in character & numeric formats

NAME

Full parish name including "Parish, Louisiana"

variable

Variable name for population density, consists of Census table and row number

estimate

Estimate

moe

Margin of error

year

Year for which ACS-5 Year estimates were retrieved

parish, parish_full

Parish name with & without "Parish"

metro_BLS

"Metropolitan area" or "Nonmetropolitan area" as designated by BLS

pop_density

Rural/Urban, threshold = 100000

org

Name of agency or organization for region designation

region_number

Region numeric ID

region_name

Region name ID

geometry

MULTIPOLYGON, parish outline

center

POINT, parish center point

Source

U.S. Census Bureau, 'tidycensus' package, see sources for 'parishes'
